      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BOOM TWO DOWN (7) had won two in a row before finishing third (22.05) last time at this track. Has a strong winning record at this journey. Likely to feature again. BAREFOOT ROYALE (2) tends to take a while to wind up, running on to place two back before spotting a start latest and finishing on strongly into second (19.91) in a Grade 5 at this track. Solid winning record at this trip. Bold showing expected. FUSELESS FLYNN (1) hit the ground running from the squeeze draw with a fast early split last time, but run over late and missed the frame when a 2.5 lengths fourth (20.11) over 352m at this track. Good beginner assisted by the inside draw. Key runner who gets his chance to atone. GOLDSTAR HECTOR (3) gets a chance to improve on an unplaced run at his latest outing at this circuit.",
